            <h2 class="text-left section-header mb-4">Trading Rules</h2>
                <p class="paragraph--dark text-left font-size-1">Follow the rules, or don’t even bother trading.  Here are mine: </p>

           <ol class="terms-list">
            <li class="text-left font-size-1"><span class="font-size-1"><strong>Stop Losses:</strong></span> 
            <span class="font-size-1">Before getting into any trade, figure out a stop loss level in  case the price moves against you. 
             I use 5% to 7%  max loss for a position and generally do not risk more than 1% of my account. 
            If the price moves below the stop loss price, sell without hesitation.  No exceptions. </span></li>

            <li class="text-left font-size-1"><span class="font-size-1"> Buy a proper breakout from a base or consolidation with good volume. 
             If the volume sucks, I pass.  <span></li>


            <li class="text-left font-size-1"><span class="font-size-1">If a stock moves up very quickly, sell some of the position and take some profit.     <span></li>

            <li class="text-left font-size-1"><span class="font-size-1"> Don't fuck around with options.  Trust me, I've tried.<span></li>

            <li class="text-left font-size-1"><span class="font-size-1"> Never let a profitable position turn into a loss.  This is stupid.  <span></li>

            <li class="text-left font-size-1"><span class="font-size-1">Don’t hold through an earnings report unless you have a huge profit in a stock. 
             Don't initiate a position before earnings unless you are a degenerate gambler. <span></li>

            

            <li class="text-left font-size-1"><span class="font-size-1">Hold onto winners, and sell losers quickly.    <span></li>
            
            </ol>
            </div>
        </div>

